    <h2 class="h2" id="sec-3-h" style="margin-bottom:18px;">3. No Professional Advice</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The content published on this website &mdash; including service descriptions, articles, guides, frequently asked questions, pricing ranges, and explanatory material regarding tax, accounting, payroll, and compliance topics &mdash; is provided for general informational purposes only. It does not constitute, and should not be relied upon as, <strong>legal, tax, accounting, financial, or other professional advice</strong> for any particular situation.</p>
      <p>General information cannot account for the specific facts and circumstances of your business. You should not act or refrain from acting on the basis of any content on this website without seeking advice from a qualified professional licensed in the relevant jurisdiction. Engaging TechBrot for services, and receiving deliverables under a written engagement scope, is distinct from the general information published on this website.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="sec-4" style="padding-top:24px;" aria-labelledby="sec-4-h">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">&sect;4</span><span class="idx__t">Scope</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="sec-4-h" style="margin-bottom:18px;">4. Scope of Services</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>TechBrot provides operational accounting services, which may include bookkeeping, QuickBooks setup, cleanup, and migration, payroll configuration and management, and sales tax compliance support, as defined in each client&rsquo;s written engagement scope.</p>
      <p><strong>TechBrot does not provide the following services:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Preparation or filing of federal, state, or local income tax returns;</li>
        <li>Representation of clients before the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) or any state or local taxing authority;</li>
        <li>Audit, attestation, or assurance services as defined under applicable accounting standards;</li>
        <li>Legal advice or legal representation of any kind;</li>
        <li>Investment, securities, or financial-planning advice.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Income tax filing and IRS representation are the work of a licensed Certified Public Accountant (CPA) or Enrolled Agent (EA). TechBrot coordinates with the client&rsquo;s CPA or EA, or can refer the client to a licensed professional, but does not itself perform these services. Where an engagement requires legal counsel, tax counsel, or other licensed practitioners, TechBrot will say so and refer accordingly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

